EXP NO: 3				
Matrix Addition using 8051 Trainer Kit

OBJECTIVE:

To add element of two matrix 
  •	Add two matrices stored in memory locations 4201H and 4301H onwards
  •	Store the result in memory locations 4401H and 4501H

LEARNING OUTCOMES:

After completing this experiment, the students will be able to write and execute assembly language program to add element of two matrix using 8051 trainer kit.

EQUIPMENTS REQUIRED: 

8051 trainer kit.      

THEORY:

Matrix addition involves adding corresponding elements of two matrices of the same order to obtain a resultant matrix. In the 8051 microcontroller, when matrices are stored in external memory, the data is 
accessed using the MOVX instruction along with the DPTR (Data Pointer) register.
The two input matrices are placed in consecutive locations of the external RAM. The DPTR is used to point to the memory address of each matrix element. The Accumulator (A) fetches the element from the first 
matrix using MOVX A,@DPTR, and the corresponding element from the second matrix is added using the ADD instruction. The result is then stored back into another external memory location using MOVX @DPTR,A. 
A loop counter controls the number of elements to be processed. 

ALGORITHM

1.	Start
2.	Initialize DPTR to 4200H 
3.	Read the number of elements (N) from memory location 4200H and store it to R1 register
4.	Increment DPTR
5.	Copy the value of the next memory location [42xx] to B register
6.	Initialize DPH to 43H
7.	Copy the value of the memory location [43xx] to accumulator
8.	Add the value in A and B and store the result in accumulator
9.	Initialize DPH to 44H
10.	Store the lower byte of the result to the memory location starting from 44xxH
11.	Initialize R2 to 00
12.	If carry flag is set, increment R2 register 
13.	Initialize DPH to 45H
14.	Store the higher byte of the result to the memory location starting from 45xxH
15.	Initialize DPH to 42H
16.	Decrement the R1 register and if it is not equal to zero go to step 4 else go to step 17
17.	Stop

